    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-22T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-22T15:00:00-05:00" n="397"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d397">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 659.119/244</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-22T20:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 22, 1918, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received March 28, 3.08 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>9183. War Trade Board [from <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1"
                        >Sheldon</persName>]:</p>
                <p>No. 327. Your 228 [<hi rend="italic">229</hi>]. <persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_CLR1">Cecil</persName> says he thinks it very
                    desirable to come to an agreement with the Danes and that the proposal regarding
                        <pb facs="0491" n="1325" xml:id="pg_1325"/> tonnage would be satisfactory
                    provided the necessary terms of an agreement would meet with your approval. He
                    stated that the British Embassy in Washington have been telegraphed in this
                    sense to-night, and I am told that the French are doing likewise. Can you state
                    the amount of tonnage that will be available at Allies’ option to put in the
                    service of the Belgian Belief if the Allies so decide?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
